    {
      "point": "Insufficient analysis of NP-generated OOD data quality and challenging nature",
      "evidence": "Lacks a rigorous analysis of the generated data's quality, diversity, and, crucially, its challenging nature for OSSC. There's an unaddressed trade-off between generating plausible OOD examples and generating challenging OOD examples... no concrete examples, quantitative metrics, or qualitative human evaluation."
    },
    {
      "point": "Missing justification and analysis of MaxProb as the confidence metric",
      "evidence": "The paper utilizes MaxProb as its confidence score... without providing sufficient theoretical or empirical justification for this choice, especially given its known limitations related to miscalibration in OOD detection. No comparative analysis with other established confidence metrics."
